WEST NILE VIRUS UPDATE 2008 - WESTERN HEMISPHERE (15)
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Wed 13 Aug 2008
From: Tom Yuill, ProMED-mail Viral Diseases Moderator <promed@promedmail.org>

******New equine data sources here******

Because West Nile virus (WNV) has become endemic in North America and
cases can be expected to occur throughout the virus transmission
season, ProMED-mail will be reporting only newly detected virus and
human cases in the US states and Canadian provinces for the current
reporting period. Those wishing to see the complete summary for virus
detection in birds, mosquitoes, sentinel animals, and equines as well
as a breakdown of human disease cases for 2008 can access that
information on the following sites:

Canada:
Public Health Agency of Canada (PHAC) human cases:
<http://www.phac-aspc.gc.ca/wnv-vwn/mon-hmnsurv-eng.php>
birds tested:
<http://www.cnphi-wnv.ca/healthnet/Welcome.do>

USA:
US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), Division of
Vector-Borne Infectious Diseases, West Nile virus human cases:
<http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/dvbid/westnile/surv&controlCaseCount08_detailed.htm>
Centers for Disease Control, Division of Vector-Borne Infectious
Diseases and Geological Survey West Nile virus maps:
<http://diseasemaps.usgs.gov/index.html>.
West Nile infection data in equine animals from the United States
Department of Agriculture Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service
Veterinary Services National Animal Health Surveillance System (NAHSS):
<http://nsu.aphis.usda.gov/nahss_web/arbovirus_summary.faces>

[ProMED thanks Randall L. Levings, Scientific Advisor, Emergency
Management and Diagnostics Veterinary Services, APHIS, USDA, for
bringing the WNV equine infection site to our attention. This site
also reports eastern equine and western equine encephalitis cases in
equine animals. - Mod.TY]

Canada
------
Date: 27 Jul - 2 Aug 2008: no WNV human cases
The Canadian Cooperative Wildlife Health Center has informed
ProMED-mail that as of 11 Aug 2008 birds have been tested in the
following provinces (number positive for WNV/total tested): British
Columbia 0/118, New Brunswick 0/44, Nova Scotia 0/21, Ontario 30/509
and Prince Edward Island 0/68.

USA
---
Date: 6 - 12 Aug 2008
States newly reporting WNV detected: District of Columbia, Georgia,
Maryland, Michigan and Vermont.
States newly reporting new human cases: Iowa, Wisconsin.

There have been a total of 162 human cases and 2 fatalities to date in 2008

States reporting equine WNV infections in 2008 as of 5 Aug 2008:
Alabama, Arkansas, California, Florida, Georgia, Louisiana,
Mississippi, North Carolina, North Dakota, Puerto Rico, South Dakota,
Washington, Wisconsin and West Virginia. There have been a total of
19 cases nationally. [These cases are unfortunate, as there is a
vaccine available. - Mod.TY]

